            . The Prisoner was <rs id="t17480420-57-deflabel311" type="occupation">servant</rs>
                  <join result="persNameOccupation" targOrder="Y" targets="t17480420-57-defend507 t17480420-57-deflabel311"></join> to Mr. Collins, and lay with me. I went out to work on the 29th of Feb. at six in the morning, and left him in the room; I was sent for, and<xptr type="pageFacsimile" doc="174804200039"></xptr> when I came home, I missed upwards of fourteen pounds, a silver stock-buckle, and a pair of chrystal buttons.</p>
               <p>Q. Did you get your money again?</p>
               <p>Lawrence. I got twelve pounds five shillings.</p>
               <p>Mr. Clarke, the Portsmouth carrier produced the money, stock-buckle, and buttons; and the Prosecutor said, the buckle and buttons were in the box with the money.</p>
               <p>
            
                  <persName id="t17480420-57-person512">
                  George 
                  Clarke 
               <interp inst="t17480420-57-person512" type="surname" value="Clarke"></interp>
